I understand that can happen at any time. But the strange thing is that neither the ladies nor the gentlemen worked. Normally and in that case what you should do is close the establishment, repair it and then sell coffee again. The employees including the manager and in a very bad way gave me as a solution, to use the service of a pizzeria that is in the other corner. I went there, talked to the manager and they told me to have no agreement with this chain, as the "manager" had said, but kindly, they offered to use theirs. Nobility forces me to have another coffee there, it was a cold afternoon. But remembering that last year while visiting Manhattan, the same thing happened to me in another place in this chain. It was at Brodway St and Cedar St. Obviously I no longer need more refusals to visit a chain of stores, where the service they give is not in accordance with what they charge. The city is wonderful and if there is something you have is thousands of coffee shops to choose from. Thank you for dedicating your attention.
